bout%2015%20cubic%20meters%20of%20water%20a%20second%20and%20provides%20service%20to%20about%2022%20million%20people.%20It's%20now%20operating%20at%2028%25%20capacity%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fclimate-environment%2F2024%2F05%2F25%2Fmexico-city-water-day-zero%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrumbling%20infrastructure%20is%20also%20contributing%20to%20the%20problem.%20About%2040%25%20of%20Mexico%20City's%20water%20is%20lost%20due%20to%20leaky%20pipes%20and%20other%20issues%2C%20the%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGabriel%20Quadri%20de%20la%20Torre%2C%20a%20federal%20congressman%20for%20the%20Mexico%20City%20district%20of%20Coyoac%C3%A1n%2C%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20fixing%20the%20pipes%20would%20cost%20billions%20and%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20difficult%20to%20think%26quot%3B%20the%20city%20will%20have%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20June%2026%20fast%20approaching%2C%20the%20city%20desperately%20needs%20rain.%20But%20rainfall%20might%20cause%20a%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20sense%20of%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Christina%20Boyes%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Economic%20Research%20and%20Teaching%20in%20Mexico%20City%2C%20told%20the%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20from%20the%20National%20Autonomous%20University%20of%20Mexico%20said%20in%20a%20study%20that%20intensive%20water%20capture%2C%20using%20treated%20residual%20water%20for%20agriculture%2C%20and%20refilling%20aquifers%20with%20surface%20water%2C%20could%20save%20the%20Cutzmala%20system%2C%20according%20to%20Mexico%20Business%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20only%2075%25%20of%20farms%20in%20the%20area%20use%20irrigated%20water%2C%20and%20most%20do%20not%20reuse%20the%20water%20when%20they%20can.%20Still%2C%20the%20study's%20plan%20would%20cost%20an%20estimated%20%245%20billion%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMexico's%20Nati